						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Svabhānu, Māgha, śu. 1,</hi> corresponding probably to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1584 January 4, Saturday</hi> (not verifiable). It records that <hi rend="bold">Immaḍi-Timmaṇa-Nāyaka of Niḍugal</hi> gave the <hi rend="italic">kāṇāchi</hi> of the tank, Narasāmbudhikuṇṭe, to <hi rend="bold">Samani-Pāpaya</hi> under the orders of the god Tiruvēṁgaḷanātha of <hi rend="bold">Pēyalakoṇḍe</hi> for carrying a <hi rend="italic">chappara</hi> every year to <hi rend="bold">Tirumale.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
